-- Sumitomo Metal Mining to Cut Copper Output 3% in Fiscal 2013
-- B y   J a e   H u r   a n d   I c h i r o   S u z u k i
-- 2013-04-01T02:09:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-01/sumitomo-metal-mining-to-cut-copper-output-3-in-fiscal-2013.html
Sumitomo Metal Mining Co. (5713) ,  Japan ’s
biggest nickel producer and second-largest copper smelter, will
cut copper production by 3 percent in fiscal 2013.  The Tokyo-based company forecast refined copper output will
fall to 423,000 metric tons in the year started April 1 from the
previous year’s estimated output of 436,000 tons, it said in a
 statement  today. The company plans to increase electrolytic
nickel production by 30 percent to 53,200 tons, it said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
